Key Match Events: Namibia won the match in the super over after both teams scored 109 runs in their respective innings.
Pre-Game Insights: Both Namibia and Oman are playing their first game in Group B alongside England, Australia, and Scotland.
Both teams are appearing in their third T20 World Cup.
JJ Smit was highlighted as the key batter for Namibia, having a strike-rate of 151 and an average of 66.
Gerhard Erasmus was identified as the key bowler for Namibia, taking nearly 30 wickets at an average of 12 in this World Cup cycle.
Aqib Ilyas was noted as the key batter for Oman, being the leading run-scorer in the past 18 months and the newly appointed captain.
Bilal Khan was mentioned as the key bowler for Oman, having taken 106 wickets in his T20 career.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
Namibia and Oman are in Group B with England, Australia, and Scotland.
